rule.description:
@IsTest methods must prove behaviour with meaningful assertions.
This rule flags four coverage-theatre patterns:

1. A test method with zero Assert.* calls — coverage without
   verification.
2. catch(Exception error) {} — swallows exceptions silently.
   Use Assert.fail('Should throw ...') + Assert.isInstanceOfType.
3. Boolean exceptionThrown = false; try { ... }
   catch(Exception error) { exceptionThrown = true; }
   Explicitly forbidden by docs/Code Conventions - Guide.md.
4. Assert.isNotNull(record) immediately after
   (SObject)TST_Builder.of(...).build(). TST_Builder.build()
   throws if insertion fails, so the non-null assertion adds
   no coverage. Assert on defaults or derived fields instead.

Example of non-compliant code:

Boolean exceptionThrown = false;
try { doSomething(); }
catch(Exception error) { exceptionThrown = true; }
Assert.isTrue(exceptionThrown, 'should throw');

Example of compliant code:

try
{
   doSomething();
   Assert.fail('Expected IllegalArgumentException');
}
catch(Exception error)
{
   Assert.isInstanceOfType(error, IllegalArgumentException.class, 'Incorrect type');
}

property.value:
(: Pattern 1 — @IsTest methods with zero assertion-shaped calls. :)
(: Recognises Assert.* plus any helper whose method name starts with :)
(: 'assert' (e.g. assertServiceCompleted, assertCallSuccessful). :)
//Method[
   ModifierNode/Annotation[lower-case(@Name) = 'istest']
   and not(.//MethodCallExpression[
      starts-with(lower-case(@FullMethodName), 'assert.')
      or starts-with(lower-case(@MethodName), 'assert')
   ])
]
|
(: Pattern 2 — empty catch block inside an @IsTest method. :)
//Method[ModifierNode/Annotation[lower-case(@Name) = 'istest']]
   //CatchBlockStatement[not(BlockStatement/*)]
|
(: Pattern 3 — Boolean exceptionThrown anti-pattern. :)
//Method[ModifierNode/Annotation[lower-case(@Name) = 'istest']]
   //VariableDeclaration[
      lower-case(@Type) = 'boolean'
      and lower-case(@Image) = 'exceptionthrown'
   ]
|
(: Pattern 4 — Assert.isNotNull(var) where var was declared from :)
(: (SObject)TST_Builder.of(...).build() in the preceding statement. :)
//Method[ModifierNode/Annotation[lower-case(@Name) = 'istest']]
   //ExpressionStatement[
      MethodCallExpression[
         @FullMethodName = 'Assert.isNotNull'
         and VariableExpression[1]/@Image =
            preceding-sibling::VariableDeclarationStatements[1]
               /VariableDeclaration[
                  .//MethodCallExpression[@MethodName = 'build']
                  and .//ReferenceExpression[@Image = 'TST_Builder']
               ]/@Image
      ]
   ]

rule.description:
Coverage-theatre suppressions are high-impact and must be
reviewed. This rule flags every @SuppressWarnings that contains
PMD.KernNoCoverageTheatre (case-insensitive) so reviewers can
confirm the adjacent justification comment exists and is
substantive (not placeholders like "tricky", "todo", "fixme",
"hard to test", or "hack").

Prefer narrowing suppression to the single method that needs
it. Class-level suppressions hide intent across the whole file.

Example (flagged — always requires review):

@SuppressWarnings('PMD.KernNoCoverageTheatre')
private static void shouldEmitEvent() { ... }

Example (compliant — reviewer confirms justification comment):

// Platform event delivery is async; Test.stopTest + CURRENT_RUN
// query is the only verification available.
@SuppressWarnings('PMD.KernNoCoverageTheatre')
private static void shouldEmitPlatformEvent() { ... }

