rule.description:
The 'Boolean exceptionThrown = false; try { ... }
catch(Exception error) { exceptionThrown = true; }
Assert.isTrue(exceptionThrown, ...)' anti-pattern is
explicitly forbidden by docs/Code Conventions - Guide.md. It obscures intent, loses
the exception type, and skips the original error message.

Use the canonical Apex pattern:

try
{
   doSomething();
   Assert.fail('Expected IllegalArgumentException');
}
catch(Exception error)
{
   Assert.isInstanceOfType(error, IllegalArgumentException.class, 'Incorrect type');
}

